Koch, 1839
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of one oblique, proapical, acute and conical apophysis on trochanter IV but can be distinguished by the following characters: low ocularium height, proapical apophysis of coxa IV shorter than trochanter IV length and trochanter IV with dorsally-curved and sinuous promedian apophysis.
</paragraph>
