</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050AFF80FF32FEBC9D194210" blockId="6.[188,1399,265,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">
VENTER (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E050AFF80FEA6FEBC9DDC4274" box="[297,389,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[200,1388,514,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-104@3.[199,1388,514,1926]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Eusarcus capixaba sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 12966), habitUs. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Right lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628971/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">FIG. 1B</figureCitation>
). Coxa I with irregular row of setiferous tubercles, coxae II–IV densely and irregularly granulated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050AFF80FF32FEDA9FEB42DF" blockId="6.[189,946,366,393]" box="[189,946,366,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">CHELICERAE. Segment I with three basal and one apical tubercle.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050AFF80FF32FE049D7A42B9" blockId="6.[189,1398,432,494]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">PEDIPALPS. Trochanter inflated with sparse tUbercles dorsally. FemUr with one mesal apical setiferoUs tubercle.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050AFF80FF32FDA3982141B4" blockId="6.[189,1399,534,739]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">
LEGS (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E050AFF80FE81FDA39D004167" box="[270,345,534,561]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1817,1843]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1779]" captionTargetId="figure-11@4.[189,1398,265,1779]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Eusarcus capixaba sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 12966). A–B. Femur IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. C–D. Patella and tibia IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. E–F. Femur III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. G–H. Trochanter IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. Scale bars: A–F = 0.5 mm; G–H = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628973/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Coxae I–IV with scattered granules; coxa IV with one oblique proapical apophysis, which is conical, short and curved posteriorly. Trochanters I–IV with scattered tubercles; trochanter IV with one promedian apophysis, which is conical, slightly curved dorsally and with a sub-basal granule. Femur III with retroventral row of about three main pointed tubercles on apical portion; femur IV slightly sinuous, with small PDS and RDS, with proventral and retroventral rows of tubercles similar to granUles. Patellae, tibiae and metatarsi I–IV granUlated withoUt defined armatUre.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050AFF80FF32FCBE9978401F" blockId="6.[189,1398,778,841]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">
COLOURATION (in alcohol) (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E050AFF80FD8BFCBF9E294072" box="[516,624,778,805]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="3.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionStartId-1="4.[189,232,1817,1843]" captionTargetBox-0="[200,1388,514,1915]" captionTargetBox-1="[189,1398,265,1779]" captionTargetId-0="figure-104@3.[199,1388,514,1926]" captionTargetId-1="figure-11@4.[189,1398,265,1779]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="Fig. 1. Eusarcus capixaba sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 12966), habitUs. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Right lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." captionText-1="Fig. 2. Eusarcus capixaba sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 12966). A–B. Femur IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. C–D. Patella and tibia IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. E–F. Femur III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. G–H. Trochanter IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. Scale bars: A–F = 0.5 mm; G–H = 0.2 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628971" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628973" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4628971/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4628973/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
). Background colour of body and appendages Deep Orange (51), pair of tubercles on scutal area I with black inner pigmentation, segments Brilliant Orange (49).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050AFF80FF32FCC59EE9474E" blockId="6.[189,1399,880,1049]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">
PENIS (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E050AFF80FE9DFCC59D0540DD" box="[274,348,880,907]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[365,1221,265,1890]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[364,1223,265,1890]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Eusarcus capixaba sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 12966), distal part of penis. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Right lateral view. D. Left lateral view. Macrosetae highlighted in different coloUrs: light blUe = MS A; pUrple = MS B; pink = MS C; yellow = MS D; green = MS E. Scale bars = 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628975/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Ventral plate with substraight lateral margins; distal margin slightly concave; ventral surface entirely covered with 
<typeStatus id="54998859050AFF80FDA9FC219E0040F9" box="[550,601,916,942]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
T1 microsetae; with 3 pairs of lateral-distal MS C1–C3, one pair of A1 and B1 and one pair of minUte D1 and E1. StylUs smooth, ventrally tilted, with basis flattened, median region swollen and with an internal depression forming a distinct groove. Ventral process spatula-shaped, dorsally and basally tilted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB050AFF80FF65FBF49D1C470C" blockId="6.[189,325,1089,1150]" box="[234,325,1089,1115]" pageId="6" pageNumber="42">
